                                        <span style="color: black !important; font-weight: bold;">Solution:</span>
                                        <br />
                                        <span style="color: black !important;"><p class="pt-00000096518551-7261-4109-9321-5bb39f43ad16" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><span class="math-tex" style="font-family: Cambria Math !important;" xmlns="">\(y={sin}^{-1}\ {\frac{2t}{1+{t}^{2}}}=2{tan}^{-1}\ {t}\ ;\ \) </span><span xml:space="preserve" class="pt-00000196518551-7261-4109-9321-5bb39f43ad16"> </span><span xml:space="preserve" class="pt-00000296518551-7261-4109-9321-5bb39f43ad16"> </span><style>span { white-space: pre-wrap; }p.pt-00000096518551-7261-4109-9321-5bb39f43ad16 {line-height: 108%;margin-top: 0;margin-left: 0;margin-right: 0;margin-bottom: 0;}span.pt-00000196518551-7261-4109-9321-5bb39f43ad16 {font-family: Arial;font-style: normal;font-weight: normal;margin: 0;padding: 0;}span.pt-00000296518551-7261-4109-9321-5bb39f43ad16 {font-family: SutonnyMJ;font-style: normal;font-weight: normal;margin: 0;padding: 0;}</style></p><p class="pt-0000003ada15a9-4093-4e39-96d0-ab0a3c5eedec" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><span class="math-tex" style="font-family: Cambria Math !important;" xmlns="">\(x={cos}^{-1}\ {\frac{1-{t}^{2}}{1+{t}^{2}}}=2{tan}^{-1}\ {t}\) </span><span xml:space="preserve" class="pt-0000013ada15a9-4093-4e39-96d0-ab0a3c5eedec">  </span><span class="math-tex" style="font-family: Cambria Math !important;" xmlns="">\(∴y=x⇒\frac{dy}{dx}=1\) </span><style>span { white-space: pre-wrap; }p.pt-0000003ada15a9-4093-4e39-96d0-ab0a3c5eedec {line-height: 108%;margin-top: 0;margin-left: 0;margin-right: 0;margin-bottom: 0;}span.pt-0000013ada15a9-4093-4e39-96d0-ab0a3c5eedec {font-family: Shonar Bangla;font-style: normal;font-weight: normal;margin: 0;padding: 0;}</style></p></span>
